{% comment %}
    Stale-assessment banner (issue #921).

    Rendered by ``cra_wizard_base.html.j2`` when ``assessment.status ==
    "stale"``. A stale assessment is one whose product scope screening
    has flipped CRA out of scope while the assessment row still
    exists — every mutation API refuses edits with 409 until the
    operator reconciles. The only reconciliation path surfaced here is
    re-running the scope screening: flipping CRA back on auto-unstales
    the assessment. There is intentionally no in-UI delete action
    (ADR-004 — we never destroy regulated evidence from this surface).

    Expected context:
      - ``product_id``: the linked product id for the scope-screening link
{% endcomment %}
<div role="alert"
     aria-live="polite"
     class="mb-4 rounded-lg border-y border-r border-border border-l-4 border-l-amber-500 dark:border-l-amber-400 bg-surface shadow-sm"
     data-testid="cra-stale-banner">
    <div class="flex items-start gap-3 px-4 pt-4">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-900/40 shrink-0"
             aria-hidden="true">
            <i class="fas fa-triangle-exclamation text-sm text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 min-w-0 pt-0.5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
                <span class="font-semibold text-sm text-text">Assessment is out of scope</span>
                <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide rounded text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300 border border-amber-400 dark:border-amber-500/70">
                    Scope changed
                </span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mt-1 m-0 leading-snug">
                The product's CRA scope screening now says CRA does not apply to this product.
                This assessment is preserved on disk but cannot be edited or exported until
                it is reconciled. Re-run the scope screening — flipping CRA back on will
                auto-restore this assessment to where you left off.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="px-4 pt-3 pb-4 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
        <a href="{% url 'compliance:cra_scope_screening' product_id=product_id %}"
           class="tw-btn tw-btn-primary tw-btn-sm"
           data-testid="cra-stale-rescope">
            <i class="fas fa-arrow-rotate-left mr-1"></i>
            Re-run scope screening
        </a>
        <a href="{% url 'compliance:cra_product_list' %}"
           class="tw-btn tw-btn-outline tw-btn-sm"
           data-testid="cra-stale-back">
            <i class="fas fa-list mr-1"></i>
            Back to CRA list
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
